There must be at least one large sized blue colored cone and/or one small sized green colored cone in order for Omega waves to be emitted. Orientation of the cones does not seem to matter.

1) Cones colored either blue or green can emit Omega radiation as long as they are not touched by a red colored cone.
2) Orientation of individual, separate blue or green cones does not affect the emission of Omega radiation.
3) It is possible to block the Omega radiation of a blue cone by placing a smaller green cone on top of it, acting as a cap. Conversely, placing a large blue cone over a smaller green cone does not affect the emission of Omega radiation.
Kappa radiation is emitted by only small sized blue cones.

Small blue cones emit Kappa radiation regardless of orientation or if touched by another cone color. A small blue cone could be completely encapsulated by another colored cone and it will still emit Kappa radiation.
Red and blue cones, of any size, when placed together and touching will emit Iota radiation. This occurs even when another larger green cone is placed over the group.
Iota radiation is emitted as long as there is a blue cone of any size within a scene.
Red cones of any size emit Zeta radiation regardless if they are touched by other colored cones and in any position.
There must be at least two reds touching and one of the smallest blue ones

Red cones of any size emit Zeta radiation regardless if they are touched by other colored cones and in any position. Neither blue nor green cones alone or in groups emit Zeta radiation. Neither blue nor green cones can impede the radiation of a red cone's Zeta radiation even if the red cone is completely encapsulated by the other cones.

1) The presence of at least one small sized blue cone emit Upsilon radiation regardless of position.
2) The presence of at least one medium sized red cones emit Upsilon radiation regardless of position.
3) Large red cones can emit Upsilon radiation when touching but individually do not emit Upsilon radiation.
There must be at least one small blue and one small green

1) The presence of one small sized blue cone emits Upsilon radiation regardless of position as long as no green cones are present.
2) The presence of one medium sized red cone emits Upsilon radiation regardless of position. However, if touched by another medium sized red cone, no Upsilon radiation is emitted.
3) Large red cones can emit Upsilon radiation when touching but individually do not emit Upsilon radiation.
